 the producer affects the success of the product to a great extent. Take the example of an e-commerce website. If there are two websites selling the same product, the success of one over another will depend on the skill of the website developer. The interface of the website, the ease for the user, and the marketing done on the website. These factors cause the success of one over another.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">2.Timing</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Timing of an idea is crucial. A startup that is based on a prospect too ahead of its time or too behind its time will have a hard time competing in a market not suitable with its product. Imagine something like YouTube being launched in the present day. With video streaming platforms like Netflix and Hotstar competing with it, YouTube would not stand a chance. The timing of an idea predicts its future in the market.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">3. Future Prospects</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">A startup should always be built with an idea having long term plans. the future of the startup should be very clear and precise and the motivation should stem from the long term go</span>als.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">4. Attention to surrounding</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">This is probably the most important part of idea development.Creating product that would help the consumers. Creating a video calling service in a rural area would be useless. It would not cater to the audience. The same service in an urban area has the potential to be exceptionally successful. The vital tip is to KNOW YOUR AUDIENCE!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Idea Validation</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The base of any successful business lies in a strong idea. No amount of marketing or publicity can sell an idea that is of no worth to the customer. Idea validation is the customer feedback for any product that validates the idea and suggests necessary changes that would make it more appealing in the market. </span>The product or service you are trying to sell must be relevant to the customer. If one can create a consumer centric product, the job is half done.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Hence, idea validation is perhaps the most important step of a startup. In order to ensure the product is useful in the consumer market, one needs customer feedback. The customer is the only source that can give honest, valuable feedback and can assess the desirability of the product. It is the duty of the producer to understand the problems of the consumer and modify the product accordingly. Idea validation by the customer can take a product from being average to extraordinary. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">One should map their stakeholders. Ask them relevant questions regarding the product. Analyse their criticism and take it into account to make positive modifications. With constructive customer feedback, idea validation can turn an idea into a dream.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Design</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Design is all about the look, feel and working of the product. It has a major impact on the way the audience receives the product since a large majority of the public is not well informed to judge the product well and they only focus on the visual aspect of the product. The basic aspects of design are:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">1. Colour</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Colour is perhaps the most important compon</span>ent of the visual appeal of the product. Imagine the Facebook logo in green. It just doesn\'t feel right. Blue is a soothing colour and produces a feeling of peace and calm which is perfect for a social networking sight like Facebook or even Twitter.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Red colour is proven to produce hunger and increase appetite. Hence a lot of food chains such as Pizza Hut and KFC are majorly coloured in red in their logo as well as their decor. The use of colour in publicity of a product has been prevalent since a long time and is highly successful.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">2. Logo</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The logo is what attracts people. It helps them to relate to the story behind the business. It creates a reference point in the mind of the customer. Every logo tells a story.</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_51\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"wp-image-51 size-medium\" src=\"https://iiitd.ecell.io/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/download-300x110.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"110\" /> Amazon logo showing the arrow from a to z indicating the wide variet of products available on their website[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_57\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-57\" src=\"https://iiitd.ecell.io/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Sony-Vaio-Logo-1-300x191.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"191\" /> The vaio logo showing the letters v and a as an analogue signal and i and o as a digital signal[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_56\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"284\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-56\" src=\"https://iiitd.ecell.io/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/new-baskin-robbins-logo-284x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"284\" height=\"300\" /> The Baskin Robbins logo showing the number 31 in pink indicating its 31 ice cream flavours when it started[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_54\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"wp-image-54 size-medium\" src=\"https://iiitd.ecell.io/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/fedex2-e1504294687949-300x134.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"134\" /> The FedEx logo showing the arrow between the letters E and x[/caption]\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">3. Rule of three</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">This is the mantra in the design creation of a company. Every notation, every standout line should </span>have preferably three words. This creates clear, concise statements easy for the consumer to understand and remember. Always remember, less is more!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">4. Use of icons</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Again, the human brain is more accustomed to remember visuals than text. using icons helps them relate to a particular tab without much effort. It creates a buffer memory in the</span>mind of the customer and helps them retain basic information.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_60\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"wp-image-60 size-medium\" src=\"https://iiitd.ecell.io/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/484361086-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /> The use of icons creates a visual in the customers mind which helps him relate it to a particular feature[/caption]\r\n\r\n5 . Consistency\r\n\r\n<span class=\"s1\">Consistency is what builds trust between the consumer and the producer. It creates a connection and understanding and a reliable relationship. Of course, the product should be constantly improved and modified for better performance, but the essence should not be tampered with. </span>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Modify it, don\'t change it. Don\'t ruin the essence.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">What a brilliant session by LeanTrack! Not only did they provide some new and fresh approaches towards startups, they introduced the concept of customer satisfaction and threw light on a lot of aspects. Of course, the samosas in the end lifted everyone\'s spirits and the event ended on a high note. The second SnackChat of the season, what a day!</span></p>','SnackChat II: Idea Validation and UI/UX in business','','inherit','closed','closed','','49-revision-v1','','','2017-09-01 1